title: Grateful Dead Live at Sports Arena on 1994-12-16
lineage: from his DAT clone of the master.  Tascam DA20 Mark II DAT > Roland SRC-2 sample rate/format converter (from SPDIF to Optical) > Mac Mini > Audacity 3.0 at 48K > Wave; Joe Noel Track, Flac & Pack: Wave > Audacity > track/label > export multiple > flac 16/48; Checksum & tags created in xACT
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, Cold Rain & Snow, Minglewood Blues, So Many Roads, Childhood's End, Eternity, Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Eyes Of The World, Samba In The Rain, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums (w/ Jerry for part of it)-> Jam-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Good Lovin', E: Lucy In The Sky With Diamonds

Branford Marsalis was onstage throughout

reviews.review_text:
killer show; excellent recording 4.5 stars, docked one-half due to the disgruntled neighbor who ruins the beginning of (the best version of) Samba.  Show highlight is the modal/free jazz jam out of Estimated.  This is the best circulating version of this stellar and under-appreciated show.  Thanks to those responsible!

Yay Branford!

childhood  ends  phil really was at his peak  its a same  and sad this would be the dead last tour  in  so cal  i hit a 900 mile  skid  on 14 year  run       music was my life only  thing that spoke to me  in late 70 early 80  my older brother ran a crew of scalpers so i had aline on all shows in so cal id seen em all most were rock  stars if you went see these bands  they play the same  set  not the dead they kepe me guessing iand they came out play in regular clothes not costumes   who eles came town middle of week  for 4 nights  long live    BO diddley to a eternity
